---
name: animation-defaults
description: "Compose animations in {{PROJECT_NAME}} use LocalMotion tokens for durations and easings. UI transitions never exceed 500ms — sluggish animations hurt perceived performance."
metadata:
  node_type: memory
  type: feedback
---

Every Compose animation in {{PROJECT_NAME}} reads its duration and easing from `LocalMotion.current`:

| Token | Default | Use for |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `durationShort`  | 200ms | Micro-interactions (toggle, ripple, badge update) |
| `durationMedium` | 300ms | Standard enter/exit, content swap |
| `durationLong`   | 500ms | Emphasized transition (cross-fade, hero) |
| `easeStandard`   | `FastOutSlowInEasing` | Default — almost every transition |
| `easeEmphasized` | M3 emphasized curve | "Look at me" moments (FAB transform, shared element) |

**Why:** Two failure modes the project has hit before — both fixed by tokenizing motion:

1. **Sluggish UI.** Hand-picked `tween(800)` durations feel laggy on second use. The user perceives the app as "slow" even on flagship hardware. Capping at 500ms and centralising fixes this everywhere at once.
2. **Inconsistent feel.** Five screens using `tween(250)`, `tween(300)`, `tween(400)` for similar transitions read as "unpolished" subconsciously. The 200/300/500 ladder mirrors Material 3 motion tokens and feels intentional.

**How to apply:**

- Screen code → `tween(motion.durationMedium, easing = motion.easeStandard)`, never `tween(300)` literal.
- Picking a duration:
  - Visual change is local (chip, toggle) → `durationShort` (200ms)
  - Element enters or exits the layout → `durationMedium` (300ms)
  - Hero transition, cross-fade, shared element → `durationLong` (500ms)
- Picking an easing: `easeStandard` is the right answer ~95% of the time. Reserve `easeEmphasized` for transitions that should grab attention (FAB morphs, sheet expansion).
- Need a new token (e.g. an extra-fast 100ms for keystroke feedback) → ask `{{PREFIX}}-ui-designer-android` to add it to `Motion.kt`, don't hardcode.
- Common API pairings:
  - Show/hide → `AnimatedVisibility` with `fadeIn/Out` + `expand/shrinkVertically`
  - Content swap → `Crossfade` (simple) or `AnimatedContent` (direction-aware)
  - Single value → `animateColorAsState` / `animateDpAsState` / `animateFloatAsState`
  - Resize container → `Modifier.animateContentSize()` (lazy way; almost always the right one)

See `.claude/snippets/compose-animations.md` for the full pattern catalog with code.

Related: [[material3-design-tokens]] (the broader rule), [[spacing-scale-discipline]] (spacing equivalent), and the `{{PREFIX}}-ui-designer-android` agent (owns `Motion.kt`).
